# Project rules

- Repo teaches **systems internals** beneath governance/medallion skills — driver/executor, SQL relational model, indexing, Catalyst plans.
- **Spark:** submittable jobs on the local standalone Docker cluster (`make spark-submit`); not notebook-first. Never use `local[*]` for graded Module 04 work.
- **Tests:** prove-it acceptance tests per exercise; `make check` must pass before claiming done.
- **`docs/curriculum.md`** is the committed curriculum; **`references/`** is gitignored optional textbook extracts — paraphrase only; cite *Book — Chapter N*; no long verbatim paste into committed files.
- **Commands:** WSL at repo root — `make setup`, `make up`, `make seed`, `make load-sql`, `make check`. See `CLAUDE.md`.
- **Package:** import `def_` from `src/def_/`; shared Spark/IO in `def_.common`.
- **Scope:** first pass built modules 02 + 04 + datagen; other modules are README + stub tests only unless asked to expand.
